<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB - TILT: 9800 - REMOVE AND INSTALL - DOOR LOCK
        ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>DOOR LOCK ASSEMBLY</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>The door lock cylinder is key-coded to key switch on the instrument panel so that one key operates
                both. If keys are lost or a replacement of lock cylinder is required, refer to Remove and Install as
                follows.
            </para>
            <para>To REPLACE the door lock, you must replace the complete assembly. The tumbler unit is not removable.
                If you must replace one door lock, replace both of them with matching locks.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove lower door trim panel. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16018_13.xml" xrefid="hl1601802">HARDWARE AND TRIM, Remove
                        <xref refid="hl1601802"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect rod end clip (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601850">Item 6, Figure 50</hotlnk>) and detach lock control rod (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601850">Item 2, Figure 50</hotlnk>) from door lock cylinder assembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601850">Item 7, Figure 50</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1601850" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1601850" filename="../figg16/G1601850.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="272px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 50. Outer Door Handle and Door Lock Cylinder Assemblies</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. LOCK CYLINDER RETAINER CLIP</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. LOCK CONTROL ROD</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. HEX NUT WITH WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. DOOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. OUTER DOOR HANDLE ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. ROD END CLIP</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. DOOR LOCK CYLINDER ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Working through lower door opening, pull lock cylinder retainer clip (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601851">Item 1, Figure 51</hotlnk>) from lock cylinder assembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601851">Item 2, Figure 51</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1601851" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1601851" filename="../figg16/G1601851.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="272px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 51. Lock Cylinder Assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. LOCK CYLINDER RETAINER CLIP</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. LOCK CYLINDER ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Rotate door lock cylinder assembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601850">Item 7, Figure 50</hotlnk>) slightly and remove from door.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position door lock cylinder assembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601850">Item 7, Figure 50</hotlnk>) into door. Rotate lock assembly until it is
                    positioned properly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With door lock cylinder assembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601851">Item 2, Figure 51</hotlnk>) in position, slide lock cylinder retainer clip
                    (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601851">Item 1, Figure 51</hotlnk>) onto lock cylinder assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach lock control rod (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601850">Item 2, Figure 50</hotlnk>) to the door lock assembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601850">Item 7, Figure 50</hotlnk>) and secure with the rod end clip (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601850">Item 6, Figure 50</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install lower door trim panel. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16018_13.xml" xrefid="hl1601803">HARDWARE AND TRIM, Install
                        <xref refid="hl1601803"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
